<subSubSection id="C36463C0F05ED879FF7FFE30CD8E7A11" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC1304BF05ED879FF7FFE30CD8E7A11" blockId="3.[151,760,476,1171]" lastBlockId="3.[828,1437,190,1173]" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FF7FFE30C8F57997" bold="true" box="[151,488,476,499]" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">
Description of male 
<typeStatus id="54C58EE9F05ED879FE97FE30C8FE7997" box="[383,483,476,499]" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Body elliptical-elongate, moderately convex (
<figureCitation id="13452CCEF05ED879FE81FE10C8BE7A77" box="[361,419,508,531]" captionStart="Figs 1–2" captionStartId="3.[150,187,2057,2076]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,1201,2025]" captionTargetId="figure-551@3.[151,1436,1193,2037]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1–2. Blepharidina (Afroblepharida) socotrana sp. nov.1 – habitus; 2 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, dorsal, and lateral view (from left to right)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341084/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Measurements: LB = 
<quantity id="4C869DAEF05ED879FD7DFE10CBE97A77" box="[661,756,508,531]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.50 mm</quantity>
; WP = 
<quantity id="4C869DAEF05ED879FF35FDF0C85D7A57" box="[221,320,540,563]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.20 mm</quantity>
; WE = 3.00 mm. Head pale brown, with some darker areas; pronotum pale yellow, with unclearly bordered brown patches on punctate areas; elytra pale yellow, with irregular brown areas on striae; scutellum brown; antennae and legs pale yellow; hind femora weakly darkened. Head with smooth surface; vertex distinctly micropunctate laterally; frontal grooves sinuate, deeply impressed from antennal socket to interocular space; frontal tubercles absent; interocular space slightly raised, distinctly narrower than transverse ocular width; antennae as long as half body length (LAN = 
<quantity id="4C869DAEF05ED879FE4BFCB0CB197B17" box="[419,516,860,883]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" unit="mm" value="2.75">2.75 mm</quantity>
; LAN/LB = 0.50); LA: 100: 56: 81: 69: 91: 56: 88: 56: 56: 69: 88. Pronotum trapezoidal, transverse (LP = 
<quantity id="4C869DAEF05ED879FE32FC70CB227BD7" box="[474,575,924,947]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" unit="mm" value="1.05">1.05 mm</quantity>
; WP/LP = 2.20), weakly rounded laterally; pronotal surface smooth, with lines and groups of differently sized punctures, and with short lateral longitudinal striae reaching basal margin; both apical and basal margins distinctly thinner medially than laterally; lateral margins very finely bordered. Scutellum subtriangular. Elytra moderately elongate (LE = 
<quantity id="4C869DAEF05ED879FD7BFBB0CBE97C17" box="[659,756,1116,1139]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.05" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" unit="mm" value="4.05">4.05 mm</quantity>
; WE/LE = 0.74; LE/LP = 3.86), slightly rounded laterally, apically jointly rounded; punctation clearly impressed on smooth surface, arranged in nine regular rows plus short scutellar row; interstriae flat. Legs with first pro- and mesotarsomere distinctly dilated; tarsal claws simple. Ventral parts yellow; last abdominal ventrite without distinctive preapical impressions. Median lobe of aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13452CCEF05ED879FABBFEB2CC897911" box="[1363,1428,350,373]" captionStart="Figs 1–2" captionStartId="3.[150,187,2057,2076]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,1201,2025]" captionTargetId="figure-551@3.[151,1436,1193,2037]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1–2. Blepharidina (Afroblepharida) socotrana sp. nov.1 – habitus; 2 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, dorsal, and lateral view (from left to right)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341084/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) (LAED = 
<quantity id="4C869DAEF05ED879FC4EFE92CD1A79F1" box="[934,1031,382,405]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" unit="mm" value="2.05">2.05 mm</quantity>
; LE/LAED = 1.98) fusiform in ventral view, distally subtriangular with rounded apex; ventral surface weakly wrinkled laterally on apical third; dorsal ligula apparently formed by one median and two lateral, more elongate, lobes; large, sclerotized and subrectangular median lobe raising from dorsal surface, laterally bent, with apical median tooth; in lateral view, aedeagus regularly curved from phallobase to apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36463C0F05ED87EFCD4FD92CD4A7D75" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="503" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC1304BF05ED879FCD4FD92CC817CF1" blockId="3.[828,1437,190,1173]" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FCD4FD92CD257AF1" bold="true" box="[828,1080,638,661]" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4BC8F05ED879FBA8FD92CC5D7AF1" authority="Biondi &amp; Iannella, 2019" authorityName="Biondi &amp; Iannella" authorityYear="2019" box="[1088,1344,638,661]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="socotrana" status="sp. nov.">
