</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2395122F05ED879FAA0FD92CC807AF1" box="[1352,1437,638,661]" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
occupies a rather isolated position within the genus, even though closer to the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4BC8F05ED879FB69FD52CC397AB1" box="[1153,1316,702,725]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Afroblepharida">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FB69FD52CC397AB1" box="[1153,1316,702,725]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">Afroblepharida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4BC8F05ED879FCBDFD32CAFB7A91" baseAuthorityName="Weise" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[853,998,734,757]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scripta" subGenus="Afroblepharida">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FCBDFD32CA717A91" box="[853,876,734,757]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FC91FD32CA947A91" box="[889,905,734,757]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FC75FD32CAFB7A91" box="[925,998,734,757]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">scripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13452CCEF05ED879FC1AFD32CD527A91" box="[1010,1103,734,757]" captionStart="Figs 3–4" captionStartId="4.[151,188,1042,1061]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,186,1024]" captionTargetId="figure-13@4.[151,1436,186,1024]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 3–4. Blepharidina (Afroblepharida) scripta (Weise, 1904). 1 – habitus; 2 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, dorsal, and lateral view (from left to right)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341086/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">Figs 3–4</figureCitation>
), as also suggested by the herein performed cladistic analysis. The new species shares the following characters with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4BC8F05ED879FB88FCF2CDD17B51" baseAuthorityName="Weise" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[1120,1228,798,821]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scripta">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FB88FCF2CDD17B51" box="[1120,1228,798,821]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">B. scripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: deeply impressed frontal grooves; trapezoidal pronotum with entirely visible lateral margins in dorsal view; pronotal posterior angles weakly obtuse; pronotal base with a latero-longitudinal striae. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4BC8F05ED879FC21FC72CD507BD1" authority="Biondi &amp; Iannella, 2019" authorityName="Biondi &amp; Iannella" authorityYear="2019" box="[969,1101,926,949]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="socotrana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FC21FC72CD507BD1" box="[969,1101,926,949]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">B. socotrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2395122F05ED879FBBAFC72CDBF7BD1" box="[1106,1186,926,949]" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is easilydistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4BC8F05ED879FC9CFC52CAC77BB1" baseAuthorityName="Weise" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[884,986,958,981]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scripta">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FC9CFC52CAC77BB1" box="[884,986,958,981]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">B. scripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having: elytral striae arranged in regular single rows (irregular double rows or striae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4BC8F05ED879FACDFC32CC917B91" baseAuthorityName="Weise" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[1317,1420,990,1013]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scripta">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FACDFC32CC917B91" box="[1317,1420,990,1013]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">B. scripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); bare head (distinctly hairy in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4BC8F05ED879FB68FC12CDF77C71" baseAuthorityName="Weise" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[1152,1258,1022,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scripta">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FB68FC12CDF77C71" box="[1152,1258,1022,1045]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">B. scripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); pale colour of antennae and legs (darker in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4BC8F05ED879FB9DFBF2CDC07C51" baseAuthorityName="Weise" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[1141,1245,1054,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scripta">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FB9DFBF2CDC07C51" box="[1141,1245,1054,1077]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">B. scripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4BC8F05ED879FAFBFBF2CC817C51" authority="Biondi &amp; Iannella, 2019" authorityName="Biondi &amp; Iannella" authorityYear="2019" box="[1299,1436,1054,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="socotrana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FAFBFBF2CC817C51" box="[1299,1436,1054,1077]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">B. socotrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2395122F05ED879FCD4FBD2CA917C31" box="[828,908,1086,1109]" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the median lobe of aedeagus is: fusiform in ventral view (thickset in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4BC8F05ED879FC19FBB2CD457C11" baseAuthorityName="Weise" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[1009,1112,1118,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scripta">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FC19FBB2CD457C11" box="[1009,1112,1118,1141]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">B. scripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); slender and regularly curved in lateral view (almost straight in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4BC8F05ED879FB75FB92CC197CF1" baseAuthorityName="Weise" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[1181,1284,1150,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scripta">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F05ED879FB75FB92CC197CF1" box="[1181,1284,1150,1173]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="502">B. scripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); with a large,
</paragraph>
