<subSubSection id="C36463C0F059D87EFCD4FAF6CC817DD5" pageId="4" pageNumber="503" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC1304BF059D87EFCD4FAF6CD3A7D15" blockId="4.[828,1437,1146,1553]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F059D87EFCD4FAF6CAA17D55" bold="true" box="[828,956,1306,1329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a female adjective in the genitive case referring to 
<collectingCountry id="F36970DBF059D87EFB8EFAD6CDE37D35" box="[1126,1278,1338,1361]" name="Socotra Island" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Socotra Island</collectingCountry>
, where the new species was collected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC1304BF059D87EFCD4FA96CC817DD5" blockId="4.[828,1437,1146,1553]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F059D87EFCD4FA96CA877DF5" bold="true" box="[828,922,1402,1425]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Habitat.</emphasis>
The only known specimen was collected in an open woodland with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4BC8F059D87EFBFBFA76CDD07DD5" box="[1043,1229,1434,1457]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Burseraceae" genus="Boswellia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="503" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ameero">
<emphasis id="B90AEC59F059D87EFBFBFA76CDD07DD5" box="[1043,1229,1434,1457]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Boswellia ameero</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
trees, at 
<quantity id="4C869DAEF059D87EFACEFA76CC7A7DD5" box="[1318,1383,1434,1457]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="503" unit="m" value="340.0">340 m</quantity>
a.s.l.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
